    <h1>Wave Function</h1>
    <p>The mathematical description of quantum systems and their probabilistic nature.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="content">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="grid-item">
        <img src="wave-function-overview.jpg" alt="Wave Function Overview">
        <h2>What is a Wave Function?</h2>
        <p>The wave function, denoted by Î¨ (psi), is a mathematical function that describes the quantum state of a system and contains all the information about a particle's position, momentum, and energy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-item">
        <img src="wave-function-collapse.jpg" alt="Wave Function Collapse">
        <h2>Wave Function Collapse</h2>
        <p>The wave function represents probabilities. Upon measurement, it collapses to a definite state, aligning with the observed outcome.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-item">
        <img src="wave-function-applications.jpg" alt="Applications of Wave Functions">
        <h2>Applications</h2>
        <p>Wave functions are crucial in quantum mechanics, providing the basis for understanding atomic structure, molecular bonding, and quantum computing.</p>
